ClientSideDataSource: openView:
The root view should be disposable.
ClientSideDataSource: openView: filteredBy:
A filtered view should be disposable.
A filtered view should initially only contain elements matching the predicate.
When an item which satisfies the predicate is added, it should be added to the filtered view.
When an item which does not satisfy the predicate is added, it should not be added to the filtered view.
An entry previously not satisfying the predicate should be added to the filtered view when it is updated to satisfy the predicate.
An entry previously satisfying the predicate should be removed from the filtered view when it is updated to not satisfy the predicate.
An entry satisfying the predicate should be updated in the filtered view when it is updated.
The filtered view should be unaffected when an entry not satisfying the predicate is updated.
ClientSideDataSource: openView: sortedBy:
A sorted view should be disposable.
An elements of A sorted view should initially be sorted as defined.
When an item is added, it should be added at the appropriate position.
ClientSideDataSource: openView: offsetBy:
An offset view should be disposable.
An offset view should initially contain only entries after the offset.
The offset view should be updated when an entry is inserted before the clipping window.
The offset view should be updated when an entry is inserted after the offset.
ClientSideDataSource: openView: limitedTo:
A limited view should be disposable.
A limited view should initially contain only `limit` entries.
The limited view should be updated when an entry is inserted within its window.
The limited view should be updated when an entry is inserted before its window.
The limited view should remain unchanged when an entry is inserted behind its window.
ClientSideDataSource: size:

Size remain constant when updating entries.

ClientSideDataSource: openEntryView:
Accessing the value of an entry view for a non-existent value should fail.
Accessing the observable of an entry view for a non-existent value should fail.
The entry's value should be accessible for existent entries.
The entry's observable should be accessible for existent entries.
Two views of the same entry should return the same observable.
An entry view should return the same observable as a regular view does for that entry.
Removing an entry should fail when a non-optional view is open and active for that entry.
Disposing the data source should fail when a non-optional view is open and active.
Removing an entry should succeed after a non-optional view has been disposed, which was open and active.
ClientSideDataSource: openOptionalEntryView:
Accessing the value of an optional entry view for a non-existent value should fail.
Accessing the observable of an optional entry view for a non-existent value should fail.
The entry's value should be accessible for existent entries.
The entry's observable should be accessible for existent entries.
Two views of the same entry should return the same observable.
An entry view should return the same observable as a regular view does for that entry.
An entry's optional observable should initially contain an observable and have `present` set to `true`.
An entry's optional observable should not contain an observable and have `present` set to `false` after the entry was removed.
An entry's optional observable should contain an observable and have `present` set to `true` after the entry was removed an readded.
ClientSideDataSource: streamValues:
If the query is left unconfigured all values should be yielded in no particular order.
If a predicate is configured only values satisfying it should be yielded in no particular order.
If a comparator is configured values should be yielded in a corresponding order.
If an offset is configured only values from that offset on should be yielded.
If a limit of `2` is configured no more than `2` values should be yielded.
